Joseph Andreyevich Pavlishak (Russian: Иосиф Андреевич Павлишак; September 20, 1923, Kaluga — September 27, 1995, Kaluga) was an Soviet and Russian painter, teacher. Member of the USSR Union of Artists since 1953. Honored Painter of Russia. Participated in the Great Patriotic War.
Participant of All-Union exhibition of the I Congress of painters in Moscow (1957).
Shortly before his death, he was introduced to the title of People's Artist of the Russian Federation, but he did not get an estimate.
